1.00	Timeball	Time ball	A time ball is a large painted wooden or metal ball that drops at a predetermined time, principally to enable sailors to check their marine chronometers from their boats offshore. Accurate timekeeping is one way of enabling mariners to determine their longitude at sea.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Royal_observatory_greenwich.jpg/220px-Royal_observatory_greenwich.jpg
